pack_module_model_libs(25.10)                    pack_module_model_libs(25.10)

Name
       pack_module_model_libs  - Packs libraries for the Integrated Hierarchi-
       cal Database (iHDB) flow designs

Syntax
       pack_module_model_libs

       [-help]

       [-cell <cell_name>]

       [-only_files <string>]

       [-validate]

       Packs libraries for the Integrated Hierarchical  Database  (iHDB)  flow
       designs.  By  default  it consolidates all library files into directory
       .libs of the specified cell.

       Notes:

              * You must specify the default central directory name  (set_mod-
                ule_model  -default_dir),  before  using this command. In case
                default central directory is moved to  a  different  location,
                the libraries can be packed again.

              * The  packed  libraries are saved at <default_model_data_direc-
                tory>/<cell>/.libs.

Parameters
       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies the cell name. All pnr model libraries of all tags un-
              der the specified cell will be linked to the packed libraries  (
              .libs) saved by the pack_module_model_libs command.

              Note:  The packed libraries are saved at <default_model_data_di-
              rectory>/<cell>/.libs.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each pack_module_model_libs parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man pack_module_model_libs

       -only_files <string>
              Specifies  a  list  of  specific  library  files to be copied or
              packed instead of including all libraries.

              Note:

              * File names should not contain path names.

              * It supports wildcard ( * ) usage.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -validate
              Compares the checksum before and  after  packing  libraries.  It
              checks  whether  the  libraries before and after packing are the
              same.

              Note: When the -validate parameter is specified,  the  pack_mod-
              ule_model_libs command will output after_pack_libs.check_sum and
              before_pack_libs.check_sum under the .libs directory for compar-
              ison.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The  following command specifies the default central directory
                name (./DATA) where models data will be saved/loaded and  then
                specifies  the  cell name. All pnr model libraries of all tags
                under the specified cell will be  linked  to  the  packed  li-
                braries ( .libs) saved by the pack_module_model_libs command.

                set_module_model -default_dir DATA2

                pack_module_model_libs -cell tdsp_core -validate

                Output:

                This   command   will   output   the   packed   libraries   at
                <DATA2/tdsp_core/.libs>.   It   will    also    create    <af-
                ter_pack_libs.check_sum> and<before_pack_libs.check_sum> under
                the <.libs> directory for comparison.

              * The  following command specifies the default central directory
                name where models data will be saved/loaded and then specifies
                the cell name.  It  uses  the  -only_files  parameter  of  the
                pack_module_model_libs  command  to pack only specific library
                files of the specified cell.

                set_module_model -default_dir DATA2

                pack_module_model_libs -cell <targetCell>  -only_files { flex-
                filler.lef  rom_*.lib}

